.TH "megasas_make_sgl" 9 "megasas_make_sgl" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
megasas_make_sgl \- Build Scatter Gather List(SGLs)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" megasas_make_sgl
.BI "(struct megasas_instance *instance "  ","
.BI "struct scsi_cmnd *scp "  ","
.BI "struct megasas_cmd_fusion *cmd "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "instance" 12
Soft instance of controller
.IP "scp" 12
SCSI command pointer
.IP "cmd" 12
Fusion command pointer
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function will build sgls based on device type.
For nvme drives, there is different way of building sgls in nvme native
format- PRPs(Physical Region Page).

Returns the number of sg lists actually used, zero if the sg lists
is NULL, or -ENOMEM if the mapping failed
